If you want to use several threads that do this for you I would use `OFFSET` and several queries (15 to be exact (3M/200K)).

The first problem is creating the queries. This would be one way:

```java
int offset = 0;
int incrementer = 200000; // 200k
String baseQuery = &quot;SELECT ... FROM ... WHERE ... LIMIT 200000 OFFSET &quot;; // OFFSET must be supported by your DB for this to work.

ArrayList&lt;String&gt; queries = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

int queryCount = 3000000 / incrementer;

for (int i = 0; i &lt; queryCount; i++) 
{
    String tmpQuery = baseQuery + offset;
    offset += incrementer;
    
    queries.add(tmpQuery);
}
```

Now we got our queries. We should create a thread for each of them, where they will fetch the data and create your CSV files.

```java
for (String query : queries)
{
    Runnable runnable = () -&gt;
    {
        // Use preparedStatement to create the query
        // Fetch the data
        // Write them to cv file
        
        // use query variable!
    };
    
    Thread thread = new Thread(runnable);
    thread.start();

}
```


