Place the path in quotes:&lt;br/&gt;
    
    set JAVA_HOME=&quot;C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre7&quot;

The error is due to the fact that it&#39;s parsing the Files in Program Files as a separate parameter, which SET doesn&#39;t expect.  Why SET isn&#39;t reading it properly I can&#39;t say without knowing more about what OS you&#39;re using, what command shell you&#39;re running Tomcat from, and so on.

The reason why your command failed is because it has white spaces between &#39;Program Files (x86)&#39; and so it starts reading the command from &#39;Files (x86)&#39;. So instead we put it in between double quotes such as the following.
try this..

    set JAVA_HOME=&quot;C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre7&quot;

the main problem is that your data not correctly send to your adapter, be sure your items data correctly send to your adapter.
you can use this code:

    int getItemCount(){
    return  ItemList == null ? 0 : ItemList.size();
    }

The main problem is here in your fragments onCreateView:

        adapter = new MyAdapter(recycler,getActivity(),items);
        recycler.setLayoutManager(new LinearLayoutManager(getActivity()));

Since when your ```MyAdapter``` constructor is called and since you are passing your recyclerview in its parameters, your recyclerView doesn&#39;t have a layout manager set to it, and therefore, 

```totalItemCount= linearLayoutManager.getItemCount();```  

throws a NullPointer exception as linearLayoutManager is null.

The easiest way to fix it in your case is set a layout manager before creating the adapter like below, simply interchange it to fix your issue.


    recycler.setLayoutManager(new LinearLayoutManager(getActivity()));
    adapter = new MyAdapter(recycler,getActivity(),items);

But on the whole I think there may be other code optimizations needed to it.

